Class GenericPacketThrottle

A generic throttler that can be used for any packet. It implements a simple throttle with no squelching.

Number of times the same object can be seen in a specified interval.

The time window to consider for squelching.

The duration of a squelch, once applied.

Maximum number of packets that can be sent during a throttle before a client is forcibly disconnected.
